Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of analog resistive crossbar arrays for accelerating ANN training, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of machine learning.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on training ANNs, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the design and limitations of analog resistive crossbar arrays, which can be considered a hardware architecture topic.
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper briefly mentions the use of electromagnetic simulations for analyzing the behavior of the resistive crossbar arrays.
- cs.EL (Electronics): The paper discusses the use of analog-to-digital converters and other electronic components in the design of the resistive crossbar arrays.
